        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cron): preserve tz and staggerMs when editing cron expression (#92291)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix `cron edit --cron <expr>` silently stripping `schedule.tz` and `schedule.staggerMs` from existing cron jobs when `--tz` or `--stagger` are not re-passed on the same invocation.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe cron edit handler in `register.cron-edit.ts` has two branches:\n\n1. **patch-existing-cron** (`--tz`/`--stagger` only edits) — correctly merges via `applyExistingCronSchedulePatch()` using `??` for `tz` and explicit undefined check for `staggerMs`\n2. **direct** (`--cron <expr>` edits) — does a wholesale `patch.schedule = scheduleRequest.schedule` without consulting the existing job\n\n`resolveDirectSchedule()` only includes `tz` and `staggerMs` in the returned schedule when they are explicitly passed, so the new schedule lands with `tz=undefined` and `staggerMs=undefined`, destroying the stored values.\n\nThe merge logic that demonstrates the intended preserve-semantics (`applyExistingCronSchedulePatch`) sits in the same file but was unreachable from the `--cron` path.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: `cron edit --cron` now merges existing `tz` and `staggerMs` when not explicitly provided, matching the merge behaviour of the `patch-existing-cron` path. Explicit `--tz`/`--stagger` still override correctly.\n\nReal environment tested:\n- OS: Linux 4.19.112-2.el8.x86_64\n- Runtime: Node.js v22.22.0\n- Setup: OpenClaw workspace, tsx executes reproduction script importing real `src/cli/cron-cli/schedule-options.ts` production code\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. Create a cron job with `--cron \"0 4 * * *\" --tz \"America/Phoenix\" --stagger 30s`\n2. Edit only the cron expression via `cron edit <id> --cron \"5 4 * * *\"` (no --tz, no --stagger)\n3. Inspect the resulting schedule — before fix: tz/staggerMs stripped; after fix: both preserved\n4. Verify explicit `--tz` still overrides when passed alongside `--cron`\n\nCommand run: `./node_modules/.bin/tsx scripts/repro-92291.mjs`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```\n=== Existing schedule ===\n{\n  \"kind\": \"cron\",\n  \"expr\": \"0 4 * * *\",\n  \"tz\": \"America/Phoenix\",\n  \"staggerMs\": 30000\n}\n\n=== resolveCronEditScheduleRequest result (--cron only, no --tz/--stagger) ===\n{\n  \"kind\": \"direct\",\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"5 4 * * *\"\n  }\n}\n\n=== Before fix: schedule that would be written ===\n{\n  \"kind\": \"cron\",\n  \"expr\": \"5 4 * * *\"\n}\n  ⚠ tz: undefined → America/Phoenix is LOST\n  ⚠ staggerMs: undefined → 30000ms is LOST\n\n=== After fix: schedule with merged fields ===\n{\n  \"kind\": \"cron\",\n  \"expr\": \"5 4 * * *\",\n  \"tz\": \"America/Phoenix\",\n  \"staggerMs\": 30000\n}\n  ✅ tz: 'America/Phoenix' — PRESERVED\n  ✅ staggerMs: 30000 — PRESERVED\n\n=== When --tz IS passed explicitly ===\n{\n  \"kind\": \"direct\",\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"5 4 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Europe/London\"\n  }\n}\n  ✅ tz: 'Europe/London' — explicit override takes priority\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The `resolveCronEditScheduleRequest` returns `tz=undefined` and `staggerMs=undefined` when only `--cron` is passed. The command handler now loads the existing job and merges those fields from the current schedule — the same merge logic already used by the `patch-existing-cron` path. Before fix: tz and staggerMs silently stripped. After fix: tz and staggerMs preserved from existing schedule when not explicitly overridden.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n- End-to-end cron job execution with live gateway scheduler (requires full gateway setup)\n- Non-cron-to-cron schedule conversion via edit (e.g., --at → --cron) — these go through the unchanged else branch\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- [ ] `pnpm test -- --run src/cli/cron-cli/register.cron-edit.test.ts` passes\n- [ ] `pnpm test -- --run src/cli/cron-cli/schedule-options.ts` related tests pass\n- [ ] Explicit `--tz`/`--stagger` with `--cron` still overrides (no regression)\n- [ ] Non-cron schedule edits (--at, --every) are unaffected\n- [ ] Change is minimal and targeted (one code path, same merge pattern as existing)\n\n---\n\n*AI-assisted: built with Claude Code*",
